annotationA: Ubiquilin, isoform A; Proteasome binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: amyloid precursor protein metabolic process
annotationB: Presenilin homolog; Probable catalytic subunit of the gamma-secretase complex, an endoprotease complex that catalyzes the intramembrane cleavage of integral membrane proteins such as Notch receptor. Required for S3 cleavage of Notch, which releases activated Notch protein from the cell membrane. Involved in the patterning of the optic lobes; Belongs to the peptidase A22A family
